.TH "__bond_opt_set" 9 "__bond_opt_set" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__bond_opt_set \- set a bonding option
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __bond_opt_set
.BI "(struct bonding *bond "  ","
.BI "unsigned int option "  ","
.BI "struct bond_opt_value *val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bond" 12
target bond device
.IP "option" 12
option to set
.IP "val" 12
value to set it to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used to change the bond's option value, it can be
used for both enabling/changing an option and for disabling it. RTNL lock
must be obtained before calling this function.
